@startuml billing-checkout-portal
title Billing Checkout and Customer Portal
hide footbox
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  GroupBorderColor #111111
  GroupBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
}

actor "Workspace\nOwner/Admin" as Admin
participant "Billing UI" as UI
participant "Routes +\nValidation" as Routes
participant "Auth + Workspace\nGuards" as Guards
participant "Billing\nController" as Controller
participant "Billing\nService" as BillingService
participant "Billing Sync\nService" as SyncService
participant "Billing Models\nPlan/Subscription/Entitlement" as BillingModels
participant "Workspace/User\nModels" as WorkspaceModels
participant "Stripe Billing\nProvider" as Stripe

== 1. Request checkout ==
Admin -> UI: Choose plan/add-ons
UI -> Routes: POST /api/billing/checkout-session
Routes -> Guards: auth, active user/member,\nowner/admin role
Routes -> Controller: validated planKey, URLs, add-ons
Controller -> BillingService: createBillingCheckoutSession()

== 2. Verify billing authority ==
BillingService -> SyncService: createWorkspaceCheckoutSession()
SyncService -> BillingModels: sync catalog, resolve plan/add-ons,\nensure billing foundation
SyncService -> BillingModels: reject active managed subscription\nunless canceled/expired

== 3. Create or reuse billing customer ==
SyncService -> WorkspaceModels: load workspace owner/contact
SyncService -> Stripe: create/update Stripe customer
Stripe --> SyncService: customer id
SyncService -> BillingModels: store stripeCustomerId

== 4. Create checkout session ==
SyncService -> Stripe: create subscription checkout session
Stripe --> SyncService: checkout session id + URL
SyncService --> UI: success.billing.checkoutSessionCreated\ncheckoutSession URL
note over UI,SyncService
Subscription activation is not completed here.
Stripe webhooks sync local subscription state in Diagram 07.
end note

== 5. Open portal session ==
UI -> Routes: POST /api/billing/portal-session
Routes -> Guards: auth, active user/member,\nowner/admin role
Routes -> Controller: validated returnUrl
Controller -> BillingService: createBillingPortalSession()
BillingService -> SyncService: createWorkspacePortalSession()
SyncService -> BillingModels: verify portal feature and\nmanaged Stripe subscription
SyncService -> Stripe: create billing portal session
Stripe --> SyncService: portal URL
SyncService --> UI: success.billing.portalSessionCreated

@enduml
